# **Freelance Platform Website \- Documentation**

## **1\. Overview**

The Freelance Platform is an online marketplace that connects freelancers with clients. Clients can post projects, hire freelancers, and manage work, while freelancers can create profiles, bid on projects, and complete tasks for payment.

---

## **2\. Features**

### **2.1 User Roles**

#### **Freelancers**

* Sign up and create a profile  
* Browse and bid on projects  
* Manage ongoing projects  
* Submit work for approval  
* Withdraw earnings

#### **Clients**

* Register and create a profile  
* Post projects with details  
* View freelancer bids and profiles  
* Hire freelancers and manage projects  
* Approve work and process payments

#### **Admin**

* Manage users (freelancers & clients)  
* Moderate content (projects, reviews, disputes)  
* Handle platform settings  
* Oversee transactions and reports

### **2.2 Core Functionalities**

#### **2.2.1 User Authentication**

* Email/password-based login


#### **2.2.2 Freelancer Features**

* Profile creation with portfolio, skills, and experience  
* Search and apply for jobs  
* Proposal submission with pricing and timelines  
* Messaging system for client communication  
* Earnings tracking and withdrawals

#### **2.2.3 Client Features**

* Post projects with budgets, descriptions, and deadlines  
* Review freelancer profiles and proposals  
* Hire and communicate with freelancers  
* Approve milestones and payments  
* Leave reviews and ratings

#### **2.2.4 Payment System**

* Escrow-based payment to ensure security  
* Integration with Stripe/PayPal for transactions  
* Automatic or manual withdrawals for freelancers

#### **2.2.5 Dispute Resolution**

* Dispute filing by clients or freelancers  
* Admin intervention for resolution  
* Refunds and penalties system

#### **2.2.6 Review & Rating System**

* Clients rate freelancers based on work quality  
* Freelancers rate clients for professionalism  
* Ratings impact freelancer visibility

---

## **3\. Technology Stack**

| Component | Technology Stack |
| :---- | :---- |
| **Frontend**  | Next.js (React) |
| **Backend** | Node.js (Express.js)  |
| **Database** |  MongoDB |
| **Authentication** |  JWT |
| **Payment Gateway** | Stripe / PayPal |
| **Hosting** | Vercel / AWS / DigitalOcean |
| **Messaging** | WebSockets / Firebase Messaging |

---

## **4\. API Endpoints**

### **4.1 Authentication**

* `POST /api/auth/register` – Register a user  
* `POST /api/auth/signup` – User login  
* `POST /api/auth/logout` – Logout

### **4.2 Freelancer APIs**

* `GET /api/freelancers` – Fetch all freelancers  
* `GET /api/freelancers/{id}` – Get freelancer details  
* `POST /api/freelancers/apply` – Apply for a project  
* `GET /api/freelancers/reviews` – View reviews  
* `PUT /api/freelancers/profile -`  Update Profile

### **4.3 Client APIs**

* `POST /api/projects/create` – Create a new project  
* `GET /api/projects` – Fetch available projects  
* `POST /api/projects/hire/{freelancer_id}` – Hire a freelancer  
* `POST /api/freelancers/reviews` – Post reviews  
* `PUT /api/freelancers/profile -`  Update Profile

### **4.4 Payment APIs**

* `POST /api/payments/escrow` – Initiate escrow  
* `POST /api/payments/release/{project_id}` – Release pay

## **5\. User Guide**

### **5.1 Getting Started**

#### **Sign Up**

* Freelancers and clients must create an account.  
* Use email/password.

#### **Profile Setup**

* Freelancers: Add skills, experience, and portfolio.  
* Clients: Set up a business profile and add payment details.

### **5.2 Posting a Project (For Clients)**

1. Go to the "Post a Project" section.  
2. Fill in project details (title, description, budget, deadline).  
3. Publish the project and wait for freelancer bids.

### **5.3 Applying for a Project (For Freelancers)**

1. Browse available projects.  
2. Click "Apply" and submit a proposal with pricing and timeline.  
3. If selected, start working after the client approves.

### **5.4 Communication & Collaboration**

* Use the platform’s built-in messaging system.  
* Share files and updates through the project dashboard.

### **5.5 Payments & Withdrawals**

* Clients fund the project via escrow.  
* Payments are released after client approval.  
* Freelancers can withdraw earnings via Stripe/PayPal.

### **5.6 Resolving Disputes**

* If an issue arises, either party can raise a dispute.  
* Admin reviews the case and provides a resolution.

---

## **6\. Security & Compliance**

* **Data Protection:** All user data is encrypted.  
* **Secure Payments:** Escrow system prevents fraud.  
* **Role-Based Access Control (RBAC):** Ensures appropriate permissions.

## **7\. Challenges & Solutions**

|  Challenge |  Solution |
| ----- | ----- |
| **Freelancer-Client Mismatch** | AI-based matching system to connect the right freelancers with the right clients. |
| **Payment Disputes** | Escrow-based payment system to ensure security. |
| **Fake Reviews & Ratings** | AI-driven fraud detection to verify reviews. |
| **Delayed Payments** | Automatic payment release on milestone completion. |
| **High Competition for Freelancers** | AI-powered recommendations to help new freelancers get noticed. |
| **Scalability Issues** | Cloud-based infrastructure for handling large traffic. |
| **Security Concerns** | End-to-end encryption and two-factor authentication (2FA). |

---

## **8\. Deployment & Hosting**

* **Frontend:** Deployed on Vercel.  
* **Backend:** Hosted on AWS Lambda / DigitalOcean.  
* **Database:** Managed on Neon PostgreSQL / MongoDB Atlas.

---

## **9\. Future Enhancements**

* AI-powered freelancer matching system.  
* Real-time job recommendations.  
* Blockchain-based escrow payments.  
* AI-driven skill assessments for freelancers.
